{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef69-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"17092"},"text":"§ 17092.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" High-performance green Federal buildings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef6a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Establishment of Office","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 60 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-12-19"},"text":"December 19, 2007","children":[],"tail":", the Administrator shall establish within the General Services Administration an Office of Federal High-Performance Green Buildings, and appoint an individual to serve as Federal Director in, a position in the career-reserved Senior Executive service, to—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef6b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" establish and manage the Office of Federal High-Performance Green Buildings; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef6c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" carry out other duties as required under this part.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef6d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Compensation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The compensation of the Federal Director shall not exceed the maximum rate of basic pay for the Senior Executive Service under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5382"},"text":"section 5382 of title 5","children":[],"tail":", including any applicable locality-based comparability payment that may be authorized under section 5304(h)(2)(C) of that title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef6e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Duties","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Director shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef6f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" coordinate the activities of the Office of Federal High-Performance Green Buildings with the activities of the Office of Commercial High-Performance Green Buildings, and the Secretary, in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef70-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" ensure full coordination of high-performance green building information and activities within the General Services Administration and all relevant agencies, including, at a minimum—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef71-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Environmental Protection Agency;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef72-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Office of the Federal Environmental Executive;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef73-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Office of Federal Procurement Policy;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef74-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Department of Energy;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef75-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Department of Health and Human Services;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef76-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/F"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Department of Defense;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef77-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/G"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"G"},"text":"(G)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Department of Transportation;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef78-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/H"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"H"},"text":"(H)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the National Institute of Standards and Technology; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef79-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/2/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Office of Science and Technology Policy;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef7a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" establish a senior-level Federal Green Building Advisory Committee under section 474,","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn004244"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn004244"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" which shall provide advice and recommendations in accordance with that section and subsection (d);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef7b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identify and every 5 years reassess improved or higher rating standards recommended by the Advisory Committee;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef7c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" ensure full coordination, dissemination of information regarding, and promotion of the results of research and development information relating to Federal high-performance green building initiatives;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef7d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identify and develop Federal high-performance green building standards for all types of Federal facilities, consistent with the requirements of this part and ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef7e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" establish green practices that can be used throughout the life of a Federal facility;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef7f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" review and analyze current Federal budget practices and life-cycle costing issues, and make recommendations to Congress, in accordance with subsection (d); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef80-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/c/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identify opportunities to demonstrate innovative and emerging green building technologies and concepts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef81-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Additional duties","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Director, in consultation with the Commercial Director and the Advisory Committee, and consistent with the requirements of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef82-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identify, review, and analyze current budget and contracting practices that affect achievement of high-performance green buildings, including the identification of barriers to high-performance green building life-cycle costing and budgetary issues;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef83-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" develop guidance and conduct training sessions with budget specialists and contracting personnel from Federal agencies and budget examiners to apply life-cycle cost criteria to actual projects;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef84-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identify tools to aid life-cycle cost decisionmaking; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef85-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" explore the feasibility of incorporating the benefits of high-performance green buildings, such as security benefits, into a cost-budget analysis to aid in life-cycle costing for budget and decisionmaking processes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef86-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Incentives","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Within 90 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-12-19"},"text":"December 19, 2007","children":[],"tail":", the Federal Director shall identify incentives to encourage the expedited use of high-performance green buildings and related technology in the operations of the Federal Government, in accordance with the requirements of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":", including through—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef87-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the provision of recognition awards; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef88-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the maximum feasible retention of financial savings in the annual budgets of Federal agencies for use in reinvesting in future high-performance green building initiatives.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef89-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Report","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 2 years after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-12-19"},"text":"December 19, 2007","children":[],"tail":", and biennially thereafter, the Federal Director, in consultation with the Secretary, shall submit to Congress a report that—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef8a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" describes the status of compliance with this part, the requirements of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":", and other Federal high-performance green building initiatives in effect as of the date of the report, including—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef8b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the extent to which the programs are being carried out in accordance with this part and the requirements of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef8c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the status of funding requests and appropriations for those programs;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef8d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identifies within the planning, budgeting, and construction process all types of Federal facility procedures that may affect the certification of new and existing Federal facilities as high-performance green buildings under the provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":" and the criteria established in subsection (h);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef8e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identifies inconsistencies, as reported to the Advisory Committee, in Federal law with respect to product acquisition guidelines and high-performance product guidelines;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef8f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" recommends language for uniform standards for use by Federal agencies in environmentally responsible acquisition;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef90-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" in coordination with the Office of Management and Budget, reviews the budget process for capital programs with respect to alternatives for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef91-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/5/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" restructuring of budgets to require the use of complete energy and environmental cost accounting;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef92-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/5/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" using operations expenditures in budget-related decisions while simultaneously incorporating productivity and health measures (as those measures can be quantified by the Office of Federal High-Performance Green Buildings, with the assistance of universities and national laboratories);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef93-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/5/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" streamlining measures for permitting Federal agencies to retain all identified savings accrued as a result of the use of life-cycle costing for future high-performance green building initiatives; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef94-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/5/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identifying short-term and long-term cost savings that accrue from high-performance green buildings, including those relating to health and productivity;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef95-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identifies green, self-sustaining technologies to address the operational needs of Federal facilities in times of national security emergencies, natural disasters, or other dire emergencies;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef96-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" summarizes and highlights development, at the State and local level, of high-performance green building initiatives, including executive orders, policies, or laws adopted promoting high-performance green building (including the status of implementation of those initiatives); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef97-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/f/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" includes, for the 2-year period covered by the report, recommendations to address each of the matters, and a plan for implementation of each recommendation, described in paragraphs (1) through (7).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef98-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Implementation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Office of Federal High-Performance Green Buildings shall carry out each plan for implementation of recommendations under subsection (f)(8).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef99-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Identification of certification system","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef9a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of this section, not later than 60 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-12-19"},"text":"December 19, 2007","children":[],"tail":", the Federal Director shall identify and shall provide to the Secretary pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":", a certification system that the Director determines to be the most likely to encourage a comprehensive and environmentally-sound approach to certification of green buildings."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef9b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Basis","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The system identified under paragraph (1) shall be based on—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef9c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a study completed every 5 years and provided to the Secretary pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834/a/3/D"},"text":"section 6834(a)(3)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":", which shall be carried out by the Federal Director to compare and evaluate standards;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef9d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the ability and availability of assessors and auditors to independently verify the criteria and measurement of metrics at the scale necessary to implement this part;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef9e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the ability of the applicable standard-setting organization to collect and reflect public comment;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024ef9f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the ability of the standard to be developed and revised through a consensus-based process;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" an evaluation of the robustness of the criteria for a high-performance green building, which shall give credit for promoting—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/E/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" efficient and sustainable use of water, energy, and other natural resources;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/E/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" use of renewable energy sources;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/E/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" improved indoor environmental quality through enhanced indoor air quality, thermal comfort, acoustics, day lighting, pollutant source control, and use of low-emission materials and building system controls;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/E/iv"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iv"},"text":"(iv)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" reduced impacts from transportation through building location and site design that promote access by public transportation; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/E/v"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"v"},"text":"(v)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such other criteria as the Federal Director determines to be appropriate; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s17092/h/2/F"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" national recognition within the building industry.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc024efa7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/140/tIV/s436"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–140, title IV, § 436","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/1616"},"text":"121 Stat. 1616","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc024efa8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc024efa9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc024efaa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This part, referred to in subsecs. (a)(2), (c)(6), (f)(1), and (h)(2)(B), was in the original “this subtitle”, meaning subtitle C (§§ 431–441) of title IV of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/140"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–140","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/1607"},"text":"121 Stat. 1607","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this part, amended sections 6832, 6834, 8253, and 8254 of this title, and enacted provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6834"},"text":"section 6834 of this title","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of subtitle C to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 474, referred to in subsec. (c)(3), probably means ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/140/s494"},"text":"section 494 of Pub. L. 110–140","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s17123"},"text":"section 17123 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc024efab-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":